- <b>Spellcasting:</b> At each Verdant Guardian level, the character gains new divine spells per day as if he had also gained a Ranger level.

- <b>Plant Shape:</b> Beginning at 6th level, the verdant guardian can use wild shape to take the form of a treant once per day (with a druid level equal to his verdant guardian level). The verdant guardian can cast spells normally while in plant shape.

- <b>Live Oak:</b> At 8th level, a verdant guardian can summon a treant once per day. The animated tree gains a number of bonus Hit Dice equal to the number of verdant guardian levels the character possesses (to a total of 26 HD at level 19).

- <b>Gaea's Embrace:</b> At 10th level, the verdant lord permanently becomes a plant creature. He gains low-light vision and is immune to poison, sleep, paralysis, stunning, mind-influencing effects, sneak attacks, and critical hits.

- <b>Natural Regeneration:</b> An epic verdant lord's body repairs damage to itself with shocking speed as long as he is in a natural area. At 11th level, a verdant lord gains regeneration 3; the rate of the lord's regeneration increases by +3 every three levels after that.

- <b>Gift of the Green:</b> As the verdant lord gains levels, he begins to manifest amazing abilities and qualities possessed by many plantlike creatures. At 13th level, a verdant lord's natural armor increases by +3 as his skin grows thick and bark-like. This natural armor bonus stacks with the natural armor bonus granted by the Forest Lord prestige class but not with any other source of natural armor class. This bonus improves to +6 at 16th level and +9 at 19th level.

